 "sportsleagueadminops.advisor (Advisor protocol, MockAdvisor +
 OutOfScopeTestAdvisor + SafetyConcernTestAdvisor test doubles, UNCHANGED
 domain content) |- sportsleagueadminops.governor (three HARD, permanent
 checks: facility-unverified, effect-not-propose, scope-exclusion,
 UNCHANGED) |- sportsleagueadminops.phase (0->3 rollout,
 phase-decision already correctly reached :commit before this fix --
 UNCHANGED), now wired into a REAL compiled langgraph-clj StateGraph
 (langgraph.graph, sportsleagueadminops.operation/build), append-only
 audit ledger (sportsleagueadminops.store/ledger + append-ledger!,
 MemStore). Fixes a prior gap: operation.cljc's own docstring claimed
 'StateGraph operation' but the actual code was a hand-rolled
 (-> state (intake)(advise)(govern)(decide) ((fn [s] (case
 (route-from-decide s) ...))))) threading pipeline -- zero require of
 langgraph.graph, zero use of state-graph/add-node/compile-graph
 anywhere in the file. Unlike some sibling actors in this fleet,
 `decide`/`phase/phase-decision` were never dead code here -- the ONLY
 structural bug was the missing real graph runtime. This fix also
 closes a second gap: the old pipeline's terminal :escalate state was a
 dead end (wrote a ledger fact and stopped, no path back for a human
 decision); now :escalate routes to a genuine :request-approval node
 (:intake -> :advise -> :govern -> :decide -+-> :commit /
 :request-approval -> :commit / :hold) gated by interrupt-before
 #{:request-approval} + in-memory checkpointer, so the compiled graph
 GENUINELY pauses (checkpointed, ledger stays empty) until a human
 operator resumes the same thread with an approve/reject decision. Also
 fixed: unqualified JVM-only java.util.UUID/randomUUID and
 System/currentTimeMillis calls in operation.cljc (a .cljc file) are now
 portable via reader-conditionals. Proven end-to-end by
 test/sportsleagueadminops/operation_test.cljc (commit / hard-hold
 (unverified + unregistered facility) / scope-exclusion hold /
 phase-hold / phase-gates-commit / escalate-approve / escalate-reject /
 phase-0-never-escalates, all through the REAL compiled graph), plus a
 `clojure -M:dev:run` demo runner producing real ledger entries for
 every scenario. sportsleagueadminops.governor-test (pre-existing, real
 clojure.test deftest/is against governor/check, never hardcoded-pass)
 preserved unchanged."}
